reviewText: Excellent movies, keeps the kids entertained. They keep playing it over and over.

I love PIXAR movies but since Disney took them over the prices have sky-rocketed and stayed there!  I was finally able to purchase this box-set for what it is worth; not what they want to charge.  Be patient, people; wait for the price to drop.  Otherwise, Disney will keep extorting our hard-earned money for their old movies!

Even though I purchased what I thought was the original Disney version, it was made in the UK, so one of the voice actors was speaking with a British accent, different from the original we had had on the DVR

Cars 1 is a wonderful movie!!! However, cars 2 seems like a completely separate movie and not a seaqual. I'm a grown adult and that movie was a little hard for me to follow (although that may have been due to the fact that I wasn't really paying close attention to the movie). None the less, my son enjoyed both movies so I guess that's all that matters.
While the discs run great and my son loves them both of the cases are cheap and flimsy at best and one was already cracked when it got here. If it weren't for that they would get all 5 stars.

My toddler loves Cars, so I decided to get him this double set. Since it's a region free version, it's going to play in anyone's Blu Ray player, but be advised that this is actually the UK version of Cars. The only difference I could find was that McQueen's agent, Harv, is voiced by Jeremy Clarkson (of Top Gear fame) instead of Jeremy Piven (of skipping work due to made up sushi-induced mercury poisoning fame). My kiddo noticed immediately that he got smarmy British Harv instead of smarmy LA Harv, but he was OK with it because he enjoys Top Gear just like his mama.
